# Board is built on the OpenAI API standard (Chat Completions, forced
# function tool_choice) and works with any OpenAI-compatible endpoint — the
# real OpenAI API, DeepSeek's OpenAI-compatible surface, etc. An
# Anthropic-compatible path (Claude, or DeepSeek's /anthropic surface) is
# also fully supported — see the second and third blocks below. Uncomment
# exactly ONE block; BOARD_PROVIDER picks which SDK/wire-protocol drives it.

# --- OpenAI-compatible (BOARD_PROVIDER=openai) — DeepSeek's OpenAI endpoint ---
BOARD_PROVIDER=openai
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...                    # OpenAI-compatible provider key. Falls back to ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN if unset (a DeepSeek key configures either provider block in this file)
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.deepseek.com # DeepSeek's OpenAI-compatible base URL (this is the default if unset). Use https://api.openai.com/v1 (or omit) for real OpenAI
# BOARD_MODEL=deepseek-chat                # REQUIRED on this endpoint: deepseek-v4-pro/-flash/deepseek-reasoner are "thinking mode" and 400 on forced tool_choice ("Thinking mode does not support this tool_choice") — deepseek-chat is the one model id here that accepts it. Live-verified: 98.6% validity / 89.7% semantic / 121.5 tok-vis / 1291ms TTFA (all PASS) — see docs/eval-baseline.md
# PLANNER_MODEL=deepseek-chat              # blueprint planner / escalation target — same forced-tool-choice constraint as BOARD_MODEL above
# For real OpenAI instead of DeepSeek: OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-..., omit OPENAI_BASE_URL, BOARD_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini (or similar) — untested here but the same code path (openai npm SDK, function tool_choice) applies.

# --- Claude (BOARD_PROVIDER=anthropic; the SDK reads ANTHROPIC_API_KEY if set) ---
# BOARD_PROVIDER=anthropic              # this is the default if unset
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...          # Anthropic API key (never set alongside ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN — the SDK sends both headers and the request is rejected)
# BOARD_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5          # fast per-turn board renderer (this is the default if unset)
# PLANNER_MODEL=claude-sonnet-5         # blueprint planner / escalation target (this is the default if unset)

# --- or DeepSeek (Anthropic-compatible endpoint; BOARD_PROVIDER=anthropic) ---
# ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=sk-...                             # DeepSeek API key, sent as Authorization: Bearer (do not also set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY)
# ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://api.deepseek.com/anthropic   # DeepSeek's Anthropic-wire-compatible base URL
# BOARD_MODEL=deepseek-v4-pro                             # board renderer — 2 measured options, see docs/eval-baseline.md:
#                                                          #   deepseek-v4-flash: validity 98.7%, semantic 96.6%, 116.9 tok/vis, TTFA 1345ms (all PASS, comfortable margins)
#                                                          #   deepseek-v4-pro:   validity 100.0%, semantic 89.7%, 123.7 tok/vis, TTFA 1488ms (all PASS, but TTFA is 12ms from the 1500ms ceiling)
#                                                          #   pro = better board validity / "smarter" teaching, but slower first visual and a few more semantic-check misses; flash = safer margins. Configured default here is pro; drop back to flash if TTFA regresses in prod.
# PLANNER_MODEL=deepseek-v4-pro                           # blueprint planner / escalation target
# BOARD_THINKING=disabled                                 # required: DeepSeek models think by default, which 400s on forced tool_choice unless thinking is explicitly disabled (Anthropic-compat path only — the openai path above has no such escape hatch, hence deepseek-chat)

# --- Optional access gate (any provider) ------------------------------------
# BOARD_ACCESS_CODE=choose-a-code   # when set, every /api/* call (except /api/health) requires a matching
#                                   # x-board-code header. The client prompts once and stores it, or accept it
#                                   # from a shared link: https://<deployment>/#code=choose-a-code (scrubbed
#                                   # from the address bar on load). Unset = gate inert / open deployment.
